Gene names were subtracted by using substr() on TR.or and used as new column first column in duplicate of TR.or (TR.gene) Dataframe was saved as TAIR_gene.tr

            col.names=FALSE)

Summary

The simpliest (in usage) method of analysis. Limma, built by the creators of edgeR (and using it as backbone) analyses data by gene-wise building linear models. For each gene there is a vector of gene expression values (provided in dataset), design matrix that serves as metadata to these values and the coefficients of interest. In analyses entire experiments as an integrated whole (without splitting data into batches). It allows to model correlations that may exist between samples due to redundant mesures or other causes. Limma does not serve as model for series of pairwise comparisons.

More on limma

Summary DESeq2 provides analysis using differential expression by using generalized negative binomial linear models. Results obtained by DESeq2 are different than those obtained by limma or edgeR because of that, for example on the plots we can see that gene and transcript of interest are marked on negative scale of logFC axis. Average expression axis also differs. To fully understand how exactly DESeq2 works one must study this publication. Some may say that DESeq2 is state of the art.

plot(edgeR.transcripts$logCPM,edgeR.transcripts$logFC,xlab='Average Expression', ylab='logFC',main = 'Scatter plot AvgExp/logFC Genes edgeR', pch=pchs, col=cols)

Summary

edgeR for limma is like Tensorflow for Pytorch. Low level Data analysis module that can provide the same solution analogous functions and results as higher level (and newer) one. edgeR counts data by using an overdispersed Poisson model, then uses emirical Bayes analysis procedure to moredate the degree of orevdispersion actoss genes. Data is modeled as negative distributed.

Conclusions

Easies way to perform analysis was provided by limma. Real reasons why DESeq2 models logFC output as negative of edgeR or limma is still a mystery to me and I‚Äôll find it out after exams
